    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera 2 is a mechanically sorted enthusiast's spec, powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus for an optimized torque curve. The critical IMS bearing has been upgraded with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal remains bone dry. Power is managed via a G96 six-speed manual transaxle with a crisp, short-throw action. The chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B6 dampers and fresh polyurethane bushings, ensuring the MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension maintain factory-correct kinematics. While the exterior shows honest road patina, the engine pulls strongly to its 7,200 RPM redline with excellent cylinder compression and no bore scoring symptoms.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 6
    },
    {
